    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
            <p>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>127800</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            <p>Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2018"/>, pp. <citedRange>279-280</citedRange>, footnote 80</bibl>, whence 
                <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/> <citedRange>68.1750</citedRange></bibl>;
                <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/>, p. <citedRange>113</citedRange>, footnote 81</bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></name> <persName type="attested" key=""><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Ἐλαιίτας">Ἐλαιίτα</name></persName></persName> <rs type="office" key="eponymous priest"><w lemma="ἱαριτεύω">ἱ<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">αριτεύων</supplied></w></rs>
                    <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <w lemma="ἀνατίθημι"><supplied reason="lost">ἀ</supplied><unclear>ν</unclear>έθη<unclear>κ</unclear>
                            <supplied reason="lost">ε</supplied></w> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="2a"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p><app loc="1"><lem resp="#rosamilia2018">ἱ<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">αριτεύων</supplied></lem>
                <rdg resp="#IGCyr"><orig>ι</orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></rdg>
                </app>
                </p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">Un tel</supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">fils d'</supplied> Elaiitas <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">étant prêtre</supplied> a consacré <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">So and so</supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">son of</supplied> Elaiitas <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">being priest</supplied> dedicated <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">Un tale</supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">figlio de</supplied> Elaiitas <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character" cert="low"/> ha dedicato <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>The fragmentary condition of the stone does not provide a clear view. However is is a plausible guess of Rosamilia's that at line 1 stood the mention of the office of eponymous priest. Elaiitas is the name of two priests of Apollo, one in the second half of the 
                   fourth century (<ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr080500</ref>), the other at the end of the third or the beginning of the second century BC (<ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr096700</ref>, l. 4) and we would have here a member of the same family, for which see a stemma by 
                   <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2018"/>, p. <citedRange>280</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
	   <p>About the name <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ἐλαιίτας</foreign>, see <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2000"/>, p. <citedRange>265</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
